==Esperanto==
===Etymology===
Esperanto ''[[nomi]]'' "to name", + [[intransitive]] suffix ''[[iĝ-]]'' "to become", + [[infinitive]] suffix ''[[-i]]''

===Verb===
[[Category:Esperanto verbs]]
{{eo-verb|nomiĝ}}
# to be called, to be named
#* ''Mi '''nomiĝas''' Vilĉjo.''
#*: I '''am called''' Bill.

====Usage note====
The standard means of identifying a person (including oneself) is with the noun ''[[nomo]]'' and the verb ''[[esti]]'', e.g. ''[[mia nomo estas ...|Mia nomo estas ...]]'' (literally, "My name is..."). ''Nomiĝi'' is used mostly by speakers whose native languages have similar constructions for self identification (e.g. ones that use reflexive verbs, like Spanish ''[[llamar]]se'').